courses.learning_outcomes:
Upon completion of this course, students are expected to

1. understand the orientation and characteristics of the Hong Kong Chinese language curriculum;
2. grasp the theories and methods of teaching various aspects of Chinese language, and apply them in teaching;
3. grasp the principles and methods of language assessment, and apply them in assessing students’ learning; ;
4. master the principles and methods of unit design, lesson design and writing of lesson plan;
5. master common language teaching strategies and techniques;
6. be able to collaborate with peers and be willing to discuss and share ideas;
7. be able to reflect on one’s practice, and to improve based on analysis.

courses.course_syllabus:
1. Rationale and characteristics of the Hong Kong Chinese language primary curriculum;
2. Characters and words instruction;
3. Reading and writing instruction;
4. Listening and speaking instruction;
5. Lesson design;
6. Language teaching strategies;
7. Unit design;
8. Language assessment;
9. Microteaching.

